Yesterday, the reporter learned from the Municipal Education Commission that from this year, our city will pilot the "modern apprenticeship" talent training mode in 60 secondary vocational schools. Students who receive the pilot training also have apprenticeships. After enrollment, they will be pre-recorded as employees of the pilot enterprises.
According to the requirements of the Municipal Education Commission, the recruitment and employment procedures of secondary vocational schools and enterprises shall be standardized, and the dual identities of apprentice secondary vocational school students and enterprise quasi-employees shall be clarified. According to the principle of two-way selection, the apprentice, school and enterprise shall sign a tripartite agreement. For apprentices aged 16 and below 18, the apprentice, guardian, school and enterprise shall sign an agreement to determine the rights and interests of all parties and the specific positions, teaching contents and rights and interests protection of apprentice on-the-job training.
Pilot schools are encouraged to jointly carry out pre-job training and job transfer training for enterprise employees with cooperative enterprises in the form of modern apprenticeship.
The pilot schools should reform the talent training mode.
Schools and enterprises jointly design talent training programs, and jointly formulate professional teaching standards, curriculum standards, post standards, enterprise master standards, quality monitoring standards and corresponding implementation plans.
The pilot program takes the training system as a pilot period. The internship time of students in enterprises is determined according to the professional talent training program, and the internship will generally last for 6 months.
In practice in enterprises, the enterprise team management mode should be implemented. According to the characteristics of different majors, a master can lead 2 to 5 apprentices to form a learning group to ensure that students are proficient in the skills required for each rotation post.
According to the arrangement, from 2016 to August 2019, Chongqing has determined 60 pilots of the municipal secondary vocational modern apprenticeship system in three batches, each with about 50 students, and a total of about 3,000 students (apprentices).
In accordance with the principle of "pilot first, then implementation, and gradual promotion from point to area", we will explore the establishment of a long-term mechanism of joint school-enterprise enrollment, joint training and integrated education, so as to effectively improve students' post skills and improve students' employment rate and quality.
