Recently, there have been several local aggregation outbreaks in China, all of which were imported from overseas through port cities.
The above notice pointed out that this has exposed problems such as untimely epidemic monitoring and early warning in some places, unimplemented closed-loop management of personnel in high-risk positions, mere formality of regular nucleic acid testing, inadequate disinfection of all links of cold-chain goods, non-standard management of centralized quarantine sites, and insufficient scientific and accurate emergency response to the epidemic.
According to the notice, efforts should be made to improve the epidemic prevention and control mechanism in port cities, improve the epidemic monitoring and early warning system, and implement border control measures, so as to speed up the improvement of weaknesses in epidemic prevention and control in port cities, do a good job in epidemic prevention and control without relaxation and scientificity, and strengthen the defense line against imported cases.
The notice stressed that all port cities should study and deploy epidemic prevention and control and livelihood security simultaneously, publish and smooth the livelihood security hotline, regularly investigate the emerging hidden dangers in the supply and price of basic living materials, and timely solve and actively respond to the prominent problems reported by the masses.
According to the notice, the port cities referred to in the notice include the counties (cities, districts and flags) where the open land, water and aviation ports are located, the cities (prefectures, prefectures and leagues) where they are located and the municipalities directly under the central government. The specific scope shall be determined by each province (autonomous region and municipality directly under the central government) according to the needs of epidemic prevention and control and announced in a timely manner.
