TIANJIN, Dec. 12 (Xinhua/Zhou Runjian)-As the last large-scale meteor shower of the year, the Gemini meteor shower, one of the three major meteor showers in the northern hemisphere, will be extremely great on December 14. People who like meteor showers can observe it at midnight.
Gemini meteor shower shot by Beijing astronomer An Jiu in Qinghai on December 13, 2018.
Most of the meteor shower's parent bodies are periodic comets, but the Gemini shower's parent body is the  asteroid (3200) Phaethon, an Apollo-type asteroid.
The Gemini meteor shower is also the second known meteor shower not "bred" by comets.
Xiu Lipeng, a council member of the Tianjin Astronomy Society and an expert in astronomy science popularization, said that, just like the New Year's blockbuster, the Gemini meteor shower generally appears at the end of the year, and the "release period" can last from December 4 to 17.
The meteor shower is known for its large flow and stability. It is called the three major meteor showers in the northern hemisphere together with the Quadrantid meteor shower and Perseid meteor shower.
A remarkable feature of the Gemini meteor shower is the slow speed of the meteoroids, the rich colors,and the number of fire meteors, which are suitable for both visual and astronomical photography beginners.
Gemini meteor shower shot by Tianjin astronomy enthusiast Yang Jing in Jizhou, Tianjin on December 13, 2020.
Astronomical forecasts show that this year's Gemini meteor shower will take place around 15:00 on December 14, with a maximum ZHR of 150 (the number of meteors seen per hour when the radiation point is directly above the head under ideal observation conditions).
Gemini meteor shower recommendation index map.
"Last year, the 'colorful' Gemini meteor shower impressed people, but this year's Gemini meteor shower will be disturbed by the moonlight, and the level of excitement will be reduced.
The 14th is the eleventh day of the eleventh month of the lunar calendar, the phase of the moon is the surplus-convex moon, the bright moonlight will interfere with the observation. Fortunately, the moon will fall in the second half of the night, and the radiation point of the Gemini meteor shower will rise relatively high at this time.
Friends who like meteor showers can observe them in the second half of the night, but pay attention to keep warm."
How can we observe as many meteors as possible?
"It is not recommended to observe in cities. Instead, you can choose a place with high altitude, small light damage and wide vision facing northeast in the suburbs or villages, and then wait patiently until the moon falls and observe visually.
It should be noted that the flow of the Gemini meteor shower in all directions is large, so there is no need to keep an eye on the radiation point of the Gemini meteor shower during observation.
If you want to shoot a gorgeous 'meteor shower', you'd better choose a wide-angle, large-aperture lens with a high ISO and maximum aperture.
For stability and continuity, tripods, backup batteries and shutter wires are also essential."
Xiu Lipeng reminded.
